    "title": "GRID3 COD -  Settlement Names v8.0",
    "description": "<div style='text-align:Left;'><div><div><p><span>The current version supersedes the </span><a target='_blank' href='https://doi.org/10.7916/fyk2-sj30' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'><span><u>GRID3 COD - Settlement Names v7.0</u></span></a><span>. The following changes were made:</span></p><ul><li><span>Added data for the provinces of Bas-Uele, Haut-Uele, Kwango, and Nord-Kivu</span></li><li><p><span>The data for Tanganyika was updated</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p></li></ul><p><span>Download province level data:</span></p><ul><li><a target='_blank' href='https://academiccommons.columbia.edu/doi/10.7916/wz6j-zk97/download' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'><span>Bas-Uele</span></a></li><li><a target='_blank' href='https://academiccommons.columbia.edu/doi/10.7916/5446-j385/download' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'><span>Equateur</span></a></li><li><a target='_blank' href='https://academiccommons.columbia.edu/doi/10.7916/w6rx-gg22/download' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'><span>Haut-Katanga</span></a></li><li><a target='_blank' href='https://academiccommons.columbia.edu/doi/10.7916/5hzh-fb82/download' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'><span>Haut-Lomami</span></a></li><li><a target='_blank' href='https://academiccommons.columbia.edu/doi/10.7916/adn6-vn50/download' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'><span>Haut-Uele</span></a></li><li><a target='_blank' href='https://academiccommons.columbia.edu/doi/10.7916/t22z-s082/download' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'><span>Ituri</span></a></li><li><a target='_blank' href='https://academiccommons.columbia.edu/doi/10.7916/55f7-5d68/download' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'><span>Kasa\u00ef</span></a></li><li><a target='_blank' href='https://academiccommons.columbia.edu/doi/10.7916/ksvr-0533/download' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'><span>Kasa\u00ef-Central</span></a></li><li><a target='_blank' href='https://academiccommons.columbia.edu/doi/10.7916/jce6-3k11/downlo